title: G-7 Warns Iran Against Providing Drones to Russia
description: Top diplomats from the Group of Seven nations threatened further action against Moscow and countries supporting its war in Ukraine.

title: China Rebukes Russia's Nuclear Threats in Ukraine for First Time
description: China has warned Russia against threatening to use nuclear weapons in the conflict in Ukraine, in a rare departure from its usual tacit support for Moscow’s positions.

title: Signs of Russian Retreat Don't Mean Ukraine's Fight for Kherson Will Be Easy
description: Russian forces appear to be laying the groundwork for a withdrawal, but Ukrainian officials warn that their enemy could be seeking to suck precious armored units into debilitating urban combat.

title: Imran Khan Shooting Heightens Political Tensions in Pakistan
description: The attack has made the battle lines in Pakistani politics even more bitter, and has shaken the country’s powerful military.

title: Germany's Scholz Puts Business First in Beijing Visit
description: Germany and China struck business deals and reaffirmed a once-cozy relationship that has come under strain as Beijing has adopted a harder-edged stance in its dealings with the West.

title: Turkey Under Pressure to Ratify Sweden and Finland's NATO Membership
description: Ankara wants the Nordic nations to curb Kurdish militants while the alliance is pushing to add the two countries, which applied after Russia invaded Ukraine.

title: Iran's President Slams Biden for Supporting Protest Movement
description: Ebrahim Raisi was addressing a pro-regime rally to mark the anniversary of the 1979 seizure of the U.S. Embassy in Tehran.

title: Seoul Tragedy Shows Dangers Posed by Crowds as Pandemic Eases
description: South Koreans are reaching a consensus that last weekend’s deadly Halloween crowd surge accident could have been avoided.

title: France's EDF Warns of Lower Output Across Nuclear Fleet
description: The energy company’s announcement deals a setback to France’s efforts to ride out Europe’s energy crisis amid a spell of unseasonably warm weather.

title: China Agrees to Approve BioNTech's Covid-19 Vaccine for Foreigners, German Chancellor Says
description: China agreed to approve BioNTech’s Covid-19 vaccines for foreign residents, German Chancellor Olaf Scholz said, in what would mark the first mRNA vaccine for Covid-19 approved for use in China.

title: Russian Attacks Leave Almost Half a Million Homes Without Power in Kyiv
description: More than a third of Ukraine’s power-generation capacity has been knocked out by drone and missile strikes in the past month.

title: U.S., Allies Set Parameters for Price Cap on Russian Oil
description: The U.S. and its allies have reached agreement on which sales of Russian oil will be subject to a price cap, racing to flesh out the details of the major new sanctions program before it begins on Dec. 5.
